President Trump announced that General H.R. McMaster will become the National Security Advisor, and General Keith Kellogg will be Chief of Staff. Trump also mentioned that he will be talking to John Bolton in a different capacity. McMaster expressed gratitude for the opportunity and stated that he will do everything he can to advance and protect the interests of the American people. Kellogg thanked Trump for the opportunity and praised McMaster's qualifications. Trump expressed his appreciation for the team and stated that the country is lucky to have them. Vice President Pence played a role in the selection process.